## 1. Business Layout: Who Buys What

Think in 3 layers: **Product surface**, **Revenue engine**, **Strategic lock‑in**.

### Core products

- Tap919 Middleman (this gateway)
  - Product: Metered AI/API gateway for agents and tools, fronted by Cloudflare Worker.
  - Buyers: AI agencies, AI SaaS builders, ecom brands with agents, internal LLM platform teams.
  - Value: Usage‑based billing, multi‑provider routing, “future monopoly prevention” (no direct vendor lock‑in). [stripe](https://stripe.com/resources/more/usage-based-pricing-for-saas-how-to-make-the-most-of-this-pricing-model)

- StreetCode (TapIDE)
  - Product: AI agent/IDE “studio” where builders design, debug, and deploy agents, workflows, and MCP tools.
  - Buyers: indie devs, agencies, internal teams.
  - Value: Every run goes through Middleman; IDE shows live credit burn and latency.

- BlackMind
  - Product: Heavy‑compute models and CRISPR‑style agent editing (think “surgical brain edits” and advanced reasoning bundles).
  - Buyers: high‑value verticals (trading, healthcare‑adjacent, operations).
  - Value: Specialized, high‑margin model SKUs exposed as `tap919:*` model IDs metered by Middleman.

- AetherDesk
  - Product: Control tower for operators and clients: usage analytics, guardrails, cost controls, and live session review.
  - Buyers: teams running agents in production.
  - Value: Observability and governance for everything Middleman sees.

This layout follows the pattern of modern API/usage‑based SaaS stacks: core API, builder surface, specialized engines, and an admin/finance lens. [maxio](https://www.maxio.com/blog/consumption-based-billing)

### Revenue model

- Pricing axes:
  - Per API call (simple event‑based usage). [billingplatform](https://billingplatform.com/blog/usage-based-pricing-examples)
  - Per 1k tokens (LLM‑native metric). [ordwaylabs](https://ordwaylabs.com/resources/guides/usage-based-pricing-guide/)
  - Per “agent task” or CRISPR edit (higher‑order events).

- Plan structure:
  - Free:
    - Limited calls per month, limited `tap919:*` models.
  - Pro:
    - Higher limits, more models, priority routing, basic AetherDesk console.
  - Enterprise:
    - Custom SLAs, on‑prem / VPC Middleman, policy engine, advanced XAI, guaranteed routing rules.

This aligns with standard usage‑based + tiered hybrid models that let you start small and scale hard. [withorb](https://www.withorb.com/blog/usage-based-pricing-for-saas)

