## 2. Agentic Workforce: Core Agent Roles

Everything we build should be callable as an agent “track” via the Shared Protocol Layer. Below is the initial roster.

### 1) Lane Architect (Strategy / Design Agent)

- Job:
  - Design new agent blueprints, pricing lanes, and offers across StreetCode, BlackMind, AetherDesk.
- Inputs:
  - Usage data from Middleman.
  - Market intel, pricing models, competitor docs. [blog.axway](https://blog.axway.com/learning-center/apis/enterprise-api-strategy/api-monetization-models)
- Outputs:
  - JSON specs for:
    - New `tap919:` model IDs.
    - New pricing tiers (per‑call, per‑token, per‑task).
    - Content prompts for marketing and docs.
- Trigger:
  - Weekly or on demand when we see a profitable usage pattern.

### 2) Middleman Router (Real‑Time API Agent)

- Job:
  - For each request, choose which underlying provider or local model to hit (OpenAI, Anthropic, NVIDIA, internal).
- Inputs:
  - Model ID + tenant policy + performance/price history. [nordicapis](https://nordicapis.com/9-types-of-api-monetization-models/)
- Outputs:
  - Selected provider.
  - Updated routing weights.
  - Log entry explaining “why” for XAI.
- Trigger:
  - For every `execute` call; runs inside the Middleman layer.

### 3) Billing & Metering Clerk (Revenue Agent)

- Job:
  - Turn `UsageEvent`s into Stripe meter updates and invoices. [stripe](https://stripe.com/resources/more/usage-metering)
- Inputs:
  - Usage events from Middleman (tokens, calls, tasks).
  - Tenant plan and Stripe customer mapping.
- Outputs:
  - Stripe API calls:
    - Usage records for metered billing.
    - Invoice drafts or final invoices.
  - Alerts when spend crosses thresholds or anomalies appear.
- Trigger:
  - On each usage event, plus hourly batch reconciliation.

### 4) Telemetry Analyst (Observability Agent)

- Job:
  - Read OTEL traces and DB logs to detect:
    - High latency.
    - Error spikes.
    - Bad cost/latency tradeoffs. [screenshotone](https://screenshotone.com/blog/cloudflare-workers/)
- Inputs:
  - OTEL traces from FastAPI and DB.
  - SQL over UsageEvent and PricingRule.
- Outputs:
  - Routing recommendations (shift traffic).
  - Incident alerts to AetherDesk.
  - “Highlight reels” for content (what went right/wrong).
- Trigger:
  - Continuous or batched; plus on deploy events.

### 5) StreetCode Session Producer (IDE Agent)

- Job:
  - Turn user intent in StreetCode into:
    - Agent graphs that call Middleman.
    - Scaffolds for MCP tools, runbooks, and doc pages.
- Inputs:
  - IDE actions, error logs, prior sessions.
- Outputs:
  - Capability definitions like `sc.agent.run`, `sc.code.generate` that call `tap919` models.
- Trigger:
  - When a builder creates or updates agents in StreetCode.

### 6) BlackMind CRISPR Designer (Model/Brain Agent)

- Job:
  - Generate and refine CRISPR‑style patches to agents/models.
- Inputs:
  - Logs of failures / suboptimal behavior.
  - Domain constraints.
- Outputs:
  - Patch diffs, evaluation runs, updated `tap919:` model SKUs.
- Trigger:
  - On poor performance, high error rates, or explicit user requests.

### 7) AetherDesk Operator Copilot (Support Agent)

- Job:
  - Help human operators:
    - Explain usage spikes.
    - Adjust policies.
    - Communicate changes to customers.
- Inputs:
  - Usage views, incidents, planned changes.
- Outputs:
  - Suggested policy updates, email drafts, release notes.
- Trigger:
  - When anomalies or feature launches occur.

