## 4. Org‑Level Layout: Agent Crews by Lane

We can think of this as four “crews,” each with human + agent roles.

### Crew 1: Monetization Lane

- Agents:
  - Lane Architect.
  - Billing & Metering Clerk.
- Human:
  - You as Chief Producer (deciding which lanes matter).
- KPIs:
  - MRR and net revenue per abstract model.
  - Gross margin per model/provider.
  - Time from idea → live priced model. [stripe](https://stripe.com/resources/more/usage-based-pricing-for-saas-how-to-make-the-most-of-this-pricing-model)

### Crew 2: Reliability & Routing Lane

- Agents:
  - Middleman Router.
  - Telemetry Analyst.
- KPIs:
  - P95 latency per tenant/model.
  - Error rate peaks and time to detect.
  - Cost per successful task vs alternatives. [screenshotone](https://screenshotone.com/blog/cloudflare-workers/)

### Crew 3: Builder Lane (StreetCode)

- Agents:
  - StreetCode Session Producer.
  - BlackMind CRISPR Designer.
- KPIs:
  - # of active agents built and deployed.
  - Conversion from “idea in IDE” to “running in production.”
  - Average revenue per deployed agent.

### Crew 4: Operator & Client Lane (AetherDesk)

- Agents:
  - AetherDesk Operator Copilot.
  - Billing & Policy explainer.
- KPIs:
  - Churn and retention (agency and brand accounts).
  - Average ticket size and resolution time.
  - NPS / satisfaction with observability and control.

